{
  "$schema": "../../../../schemas/workspace/warm_start_conformance.schema.json",
  "corpus_id": "workspace.warm_start_and_live_resume.beta",
  "schema_version": 1,
  "description": "Conformance, interoperability, operations/deployment, failure / recovery, and design-QA drill corpus for the M3 warm-start, prebuild, and live-resume beta boundary owned by aureline-shell (validate_warm_start_choice_card / WarmStartChoiceCard in start_center::warm_start_choice). This manifest is the single source of truth: every positive drill loads one warm-start choice card, requires it to be contract-valid, holds the cross-cutting warm-start safety invariants (a local-safe default, no lane that runs setup or widens trust without review, a same-weight Open-minimal path on every card, both same-weight escape hatches on local-first cards, a stale snapshot that can never back a live resume, redaction safety), and matches every pinned expectation below; every negative drill applies a typed tamper to a contract-valid base card and MUST raise a finding containing expected_failure_substring. The corpus proves the M3 warm-start exit-gate: template, prebuild, snapshot-resume, live-workspace-resume, clone-fresh, open-minimal, and set-up-later rows stay distinct, inspectable choices that disclose source class, support class, runtime/host class, exact setup actions, snapshot age and freshness, invalidation reason, and whether the next action is Resume live, Start from snapshot, Clone fresh, Open minimal, or Set up later; stale, mirror-unverified, offline, and policy-narrowed starters degrade to precise states instead of a generic setup failure; and no warm-start path silently widens trust, installs packages, runs setup tasks, or masquerades a remote/managed lane as a local open.",
